---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Closed Caption Generator Free — SRT, VTT, Accessibility | AudioSRT" description="Generate closed captions for any video for free. Export SRT or VTT for accessibility compliance, or burn open captions directly into your video." canonical="https://audiosrt.com/tools/closed-caption-generator">
  <Header />
  <main class="lp-main">

    <section class="lp-hero">
      <span class="lp-badge">Accessibility · SRT · VTT · Open Captions</span>
      <h1 class="lp-h1">Closed Caption Generator<br><span class="lp-accent">Free Online Tool</span></h1>
      <p class="lp-intro">
        Closed captions and open captions are often confused, but they serve different purposes. Closed captions are delivered as a separate file — SRT or VTT — that the viewer can toggle on or off depending on the platform. Open captions are burned directly into the video frame, always visible regardless of whether the player supports caption tracks. AudioSRT generates both from the same transcript.
      </p>
      <p class="lp-intro">
        For educators creating course content, communications teams publishing to corporate intranets, or anyone producing public-facing video, closed captions are a core accessibility requirement under WCAG 2.1 and ADA guidelines. Generating them accurately — and reviewing them before publishing — is what AudioSRT is designed for. Export your SRT or VTT file, upload it alongside your video, and your content meets the baseline requirement.
      </p>
      <a href="/tool" class="lp-cta">Generate closed captions →</a>
    </section>

    <section class="lp-steps-section" style="margin: 0 auto 48px;">
      <h2>How it works</h2>
      <div class="lp-steps">
        <div class="lp-step">
          <div class="lp-step-num">01</div>
          <h3>Upload your video or audio</h3>
          <p>Load any video or audio format. The file is processed entirely in your browser — no upload to a server, which matters when you're working with internal or unpublished content.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-step">
          <div class="lp-step-num">02</div>
          <h3>Transcribe and time the captions</h3>
          <p>Whisper produces word-level timestamps for precise caption timing. Review the transcript and correct any errors before you publish — accuracy matters more for accessibility captions than for internal notes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-step">
          <div class="lp-step-num">03</div>
          <h3>Export closed or open captions</h3>
          <p>Choose SRT or VTT for platforms that support caption track upload (YouTube, Vimeo, LMS platforms). Or export a burned-in MP4 for platforms that don't — social media, direct file distribution, embedded players.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="lp-features">
      <h2>What's included</h2>
      <div class="lp-feature-grid">
        <div class="lp-feature-card">
          <div class="lp-feature-icon">♿</div>
          <h3>Accessibility compliance support</h3>
          <p>Generate the SRT or VTT files needed to meet WCAG 2.1 Level AA and ADA Section 508 captioning requirements for publicly accessible educational and government video content.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-feature-card">
          <div class="lp-feature-icon">📁</div>
          <h3>Closed captions: SRT and VTT</h3>
          <p>Export standard caption files compatible with YouTube, Vimeo, Canvas, Brightcove, Panopto, and most LMS and video hosting platforms that accept caption track uploads.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-feature-card">
          <div class="lp-feature-icon">🎬</div>
          <h3>Open captions: burned-in video</h3>
          <p>For platforms with no caption upload support — social video, standalone MP4 files, digital signage — export a finished video with captions permanently embedded in the frame.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-feature-card">
          <div class="lp-feature-icon">✏️</div>
          <h3>Review before publishing</h3>
          <p>Edit the transcript for accuracy before export. For accessibility use, caption quality matters — inaccurate auto-generated captions that aren't reviewed don't satisfy compliance requirements.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="lp-cta-section">
      <h2>Generate closed captions now</h2>
      <p>Free to start. Video captions on the Starter plan — 14-day trial included.</p>
      <a href="/tool" class="lp-cta">Start for free →</a>
    </section>

  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.lp-main { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: #1D1D1F; }
.lp-hero { text-align: center; padding: 80px 20px 60px; max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; }
.lp-badge { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; background: #EEEFFD; color: #6366F1; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 500; padding: 5px 14px; border-radius: 20px; border: 0.5px solid #C7C8F9; margin-bottom: 24px; }
.lp-h1 { font-size: clamp(28px, 4.5vw, 46px); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.15; letter-spacing: -0.8px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.lp-accent { color: #6366F1; }
.lp-intro { font-size: 15px; color: #6E6E73; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 560px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; }
.lp-cta { display: inline-block; background: #6366F1; color: #fff; padding: 13px 28px; border-radius: 10px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 500; text-decoration: none; transition: background 0.15s; }
.lp-cta:hover { background: #4F46E5; }
.lp-steps-section { padding: 64px 20px; max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; background: #F5F5F7; border-radius: 24px; text-align: center; }
.lp-steps-section h2 { font-size: 26px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 40px; letter-spacing: -0.5px; }
.lp-steps { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 32px; text-align: left; }
@media (max-width: 768px) { .lp-steps { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
.lp-step-num { font-size: 44px; font-weight: 800; color: #EEEFFD; letter-spacing: -2px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.lp-step h3 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.lp-step p { font-size: 13px; color: #6E6E73; line-height: 1.6; }
.lp-features { padding: 64px 20px; max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; }
.lp-features h2 { font-size: 26px; font-weight: 700; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 36px; letter-spacing: -0.5px; }
.lp-feature-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 20px; }
@media (max-width: 600px) { .lp-feature-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
.lp-feature-card { background: #fff; border: 0.5px solid #E5E5E7; border-radius: 14px; padding: 24px; }
.lp-feature-icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.lp-feature-card h3 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.lp-feature-card p { font-size: 13px; color: #6E6E73; line-height: 1.6; }
.lp-cta-section { text-align: center; padding: 64px 20px 80px; }
.lp-cta-section h2 { font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.lp-cta-section p { font-size: 14px; color: #6E6E73; margin-bottom: 24px; }
.lp-body { font-size: 14px; color: #3D3D3F; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 14px; }
.lp-detail { max-width: 680px; margin: 64px auto; padding: 0 20px; }
.lp-detail h2 { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.lp-inline-link { color: #6366F1; text-decoration: none; }
.lp-inline-link:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
</style>
